owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

premium(string,uint256,uint256).details: Returns the pricing premium in wei.

price(string,uint256,uint256).details: Returns the price to register or renew a name.

params.duration: How long the name is being registered or extended for, in seconds.
params.expires: When the name presently expires (0 if this is a new registration).
params.name: The name being registered or renewed.

returns._0: The price of this renewal or registration, in wei.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._usdOracle: The address of the price oracle to use.

params._rentPrices: The price array. Each element corresponds to a specific                    name length; names longer than the length of the array                    default to the price of the last element. Values are                    in base price units, equal to one attodollar (1e-18                    dollar) each.

timeUntilPremium(uint256,uint256).details: Returns the timestamp at which a name with the specified expiry date will have      the specified re-registration price premium.

params.amount: The amount, in wei, the caller is willing to pay
params.expires: The timestamp at which the name expires.

returns._0: The timestamp at which the premium for this domain will be `amount`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
